revision.text:
'''Tenpaku''' (天白, also pronounced Amashiro) refers to various place names in Japan, derived from {{ill|Tenpaku faith|ja|天白信仰}}.

== Names ==
* Tenpaku – A Japanese {{ill|surname|ja|姓}}.
** {{ill|Kanade Tenpaku|ja|天白奏音}} ({{ill|child actor|ja|子役}})
** {{ill|Shōran Tenpaku|ja|天白松嵐}} (dye artist and painter)

== Place Names ==
;Municipalities and Administrative Districts
* {{ill|Tenpaku Ward|ja|天白区}} – An administrative ward of {{ill|Nagoya City|ja|名古屋市}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}}.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Village (Aichi)|ja|天白村 (愛知県)}} – A former village in {{ill|Aichi District (Aichi Prefecture)|ja|愛知郡 (愛知県)}}, now part of Nagoya City.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Village (Mie)|ja|天白村 (三重県)}} – A former village in {{ill|Ichishi District|ja|一志郡}}, now part of {{ill|Matsusaka City|ja|松阪市}}.

;Towns and Districts
* {{ill|Tenpaku Town (Okazaki City)|ja|天白町 (岡崎市)}} – A town in {{ill|Okazaki City|ja|岡崎市}}, Aichi Prefecture.
* {{ill|Narumi Town (Nagoya City)|ja|鳴海町 (名古屋市)}} Tenpaku – A sub-district of {{ill|Midori Ward (Nagoya)|ja|緑区 (名古屋市)}}, Nagoya City.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Town (Nagoya City)|ja|天白町 (名古屋市)}} – A district in {{ill|Minami Ward (Nagoya)|ja|南区 (名古屋市)}}.
* Tenpaku Town (Nagoya City, Former Tenpaku Village) – Includes:
  ** {{ill|Tenpaku Town Yagoto|ja|天白町八事}}
  ** {{ill|Tenpaku Town Shimada|ja|天白町島田}}
  ** {{ill|Tenpaku Town Hirabari|ja|天白町平針}}
  ** {{ill|Tenpaku Town Ueda|ja|天白町植田}}
  ** {{ill|Tenpaku Town Nonami|ja|天白町野並}}
* Haruki Tenpaku – A sub-district in {{ill|Tōgō Town|ja|東郷町}}, Aichi District.

;Rivers and Lakes
* {{ill|Tenpaku River (Aichi)|ja|天白川 (愛知県)}} – A Class 2 river flowing through Nagoya, Tokai, and Nisshin in Aichi Prefecture.
* {{ill|Tenpaku River (Tahara)|ja|天白川 (田原市)}} – A Class 2 river in {{ill|Tahara City|ja|田原市}}, Aichi Prefecture.
* Tenpaku River (Higashiura Town) – A small river in {{ill|Higashiura Town|ja|東浦町}}, Chita District, Aichi Prefecture.
* {{ill|Tenpaku River (Mie)|ja|天白川 (三重県)}} – A Class 2 river in {{ill|Yokkaichi City|ja|四日市市}}, Mie Prefecture.
* Tenpaku Irrigation – A former canal in Aichi Prefecture.
* {{ill|Lower Pond of Tenpaku Gorge|ja|天白渓#下池}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Gorge Wetland|ja|天白渓#天白渓湿地}}

;Other Locations
* {{ill|Tenpaku Gorge|ja|天白渓}}

== Facilities ==
* {{ill|Nagoya City Tenpaku Elementary School|ja|名古屋市立天白小学校}}
* {{ill|Nagoya City Tenpaku Junior High School|ja|名古屋市立天白中学校}}
* {{ill|Nagoya City Minami-Tenpaku Junior High School|ja|名古屋市立南天白中学校}}
* {{ill|Aichi Prefectural Tenpaku High School|ja|愛知県立天白高等学校}}
* {{ill|Matsusaka City Tenpaku Elementary School|ja|松阪市立天白小学校}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Park (Aichi)|ja|天白公園 (愛知県)}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Park (Takamori Town)|ja|天白公園 (高森町)}} – A park in {{ill|Takamori Town (Nagano)|ja|高森町 (長野県)}}, Shimoina District, Nagano Prefecture.
* Tenpaku Park (Nagiso Town) – A park in {{ill|Nagiso Town|ja|南木曽町}}, Kiso District, Nagano Prefecture.
* {{ill|Tenpaku River Green Space|ja|天白川緑地}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Sports Center|ja|天白スポーツセンター}}
* {{ill|Nagoya City Tenpaku Library|ja|名古屋市天白図書館}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Police Station|ja|天白警察署}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Fire Station|ja|天白消防署}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Post Office|ja|天白郵便局}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Goshōkō|ja|天白護床工}}
* Tenpaku Field Practice Area – A former practice ground in Toyohashi City, Aichi Prefecture, also known as {{ill|Tenpaku Hara Field Practice Area|ja|天伯原演習場}}.

== Other ==
* Tenpaku Tumulus
* {{ill|Tenpaku Iwakura Ruins|ja|天白磐座遺跡}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Ruins|ja|天白遺跡}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku God|ja|天白神}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Faith|ja|天白信仰}}
* {{ill|Tenpaku Hatori no Mikoto|ja|天白羽鳥命}} – Another name for {{ill|Naga Hatori no Kami|ja|長白羽神}}.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Hatori no Kami|ja|天白羽鳥神}} – Another name for Naga Hatori no Kami.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Credit Agricultural Cooperative|ja|天白信用農業協同組合}}

