'''Tenpaku''' (天白, also pronounced Amashiro) refers to various place names in Japan, derived from {{ill|Tenpaku faith|ja|天白信仰|12=draft}}.

== Names ==
* Tenpaku – A Japanese {{ill|surname|ja|姓|12=draft}}.
** {{ill|Kanade Tenpaku|ja|天白奏音|12=draft}} ({{ill|child actor|ja|子役|12=draft}})
** {{ill|Shōran Tenpaku|ja|天白松嵐|12=draft}} (dye artist and painter)

== Place Names ==
;Municipalities and Administrative Districts
* {{ill|Tenpaku Ward|ja|天白区|12=draft}} – An administrative ward of {{ill|Nagoya City|ja|名古屋市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Village (Aichi)|ja|天白村 (愛知県)|12=draft}} – A former village in {{ill|Aichi District (Aichi Prefecture)|ja|愛知郡 (愛知県)|12=draft}}, now part of Nagoya City.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Village (Mie)|ja|天白村 (三重県)|12=draft}} – A former village in {{ill|Ichishi District|ja|一志郡|12=draft}}, now part of {{ill|Matsusaka City|ja|松阪市|12=draft}}.

;Towns and Districts
* {{ill|Tenpaku Town (Okazaki City)|ja|天白町 (岡崎市)|12=draft}} – A town in {{ill|Okazaki City|ja|岡崎市|12=draft}}, Aichi Prefecture.
* {{ill|Narumi Town (Nagoya City)|ja|鳴海町 (名古屋市)|12=draft}} Tenpaku – A sub-district of {{ill|Midori Ward (Nagoya)|ja|緑区 (名古屋市)|12=draft}}, Nagoya City.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Town (Nagoya City)|ja|天白町 (名古屋市)|12=draft}} – A district in {{ill|Minami Ward (Nagoya)|ja|南区 (名古屋市)|12=draft}}.
